# STAQPRO-340 — real trace data is operator-local. Committed in this repo:
#   - README.md per version dir
#   - manifest.example.json (synthetic schema reference)
#   - The build script (scripts/build-trace-set.ts) and types
#     (lib/eval/trace-set.ts) — those live outside this dir.
#
# Operator-generated, NOT committed:
#   - manifest.json (the real one, SHA-pinned against real traces)
#   - *.trace.json (real customer-bodied traces)
#
# Rationale: real bodies (even PII-scrubbed per lib/rag/scrub.ts) violate the
# project privacy constraint that bars committed customer email content. The
# operator regenerates the JSONL from the source appliance DB before each
# eval run (see t2-traces/v1.0/README.md).

*.trace.json
manifest.json

# Don't ignore the schema-reference manifest. The negation comes after the
# include so .gitignore's last-match-wins rule keeps it tracked.
!manifest.example.json
